<h3>Peak Drinking Windows</h3>
<p>Fruit-forward styles from warm climates peak at 1-3 years when vibrant fruit balances with softened tannins. Cooler climate expressions reach their stride at 3-5 years, while more structured examples hit their peak at 4-7 years when all elements harmonize.</p>

<h3>Storage Requirements</h3>
<p>Maintain consistent <strong>55-60°F temperature</strong> with 60-70% humidity. Store bottles horizontally to keep corks moist, away from light and vibration. Even inexpensive Cabernets benefit from proper cellaring conditions.</p>

<h3>Aging vs. Spoilage</h3>
<p>Properly aged Cabernet shows integrated tannins, complex aromatics, and balanced acidity. Warning signs include browning at the rim (premature oxidation), vinegar aromas (acetic acid), or musty cork taint. Most sub-$20 Cabernets should show improvement within their first 3-5 years rather than declining.</p>

